led Nuclear Disaster |work=Online.wsj.com |date=1 July 2011 |accessdate=13 July 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110704060252/http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052702304887904576395580035481822.html |archivedate=4 July 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"WSJ20120723\">{{cite news |title=Japan Panel Says Plant Operator Falls Short on Nuclear Safety |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10000872396390444025204577544732979462706 |accessdate=30 July 2012 |newspaper=The Wall Street Journal |date=23 July 2012 |author1=Mitsuru Obe |author2=Eleanor Warnock |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130927120309/http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10000872396390444025204577544732979462706.html |archivedate= 27 September 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"www\">{{in lang|nl}} Nu.nl (26 October 2012) [http://www.nu.nl/buitenland/2943442/tepco-sluit-niet-centrale-fukushima-nog-lekt.html Tepco sluit niet uit dat centrale Fukushima nog lekt] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140108032351/http://www.nu.nl/buitenland/2943442/tepco-sluit-niet-centrale-fukushima-nog-lekt.html |date=8 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"www17\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.un.org/en/story/2012/08/417412-japanese-nuclear-plant-remarkably-undamaged-earthquake-un-atomic-agency|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029185251/http://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=42664&Cr=iaea&Cr1#.UV5n_crpyJM|url-status = dead|title=Japanese nuclear plant 'remarkably undamaged' in earthquake \u2013 UN atomic agency|date=10 August 2012|archivedate=29 October 2013|website=UN News}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"www19\">(dutch)''Nu.nl'' (22 August 2011)[http://www.nu.nl/buitenland/2595112/gebied-fukushima-mogelijk-decennia-verboden.html Area around Fukushima maybe a forbidden zone for decades to come] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023044023/http://www.nu.nl/buitenland/2595112/gebied-fukushima-mogelijk-decennia-verboden.html |date=23 October 2013}}</ref>\