s (mSv) per hour radiation dose observed at Fukushima Daiichi occurred between 1s 3 and 4. This is a high dose-level value, but it is a local value at a single location and at a certain point in time. The IAEA continues to confirm the evolution and value of this dose rate. It should be noted that because of this detected value, non-indispensable staff was evacuated from the plant, in line with the Emergency Response Plan, and that the population around the plant is already evacuated. |accessdate=16 March 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110314165946/http://www.iaea.org/newscenter/news/tsunamiupdate01.html |archivedate=14 March 2011 |url-status=live |date=June 2011 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NISA61\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nisa.meti.go.jp/english/files/en20110330-1-1.pdf |title=Seismic Damage Information (the 61st Release) |date=29 March 2011 |work=Nuclear and Industrial Safety Agency |accessdate=12 April 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110501090740/http://www.nisa.meti.go.jp/english/files/en20110330-1-1.pdf |archivedate=1 May 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"world-nuclear-news.org\">{{cite web |title=Spraying continues at Fukushima Daiichi |url=http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS_Spraying_continues_at_Fukushima_Daiichi_1803111.html |accessdate=19 March 2011 |date=18 March 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110319003615/http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS_Spraying_continues_at_Fukushima_Daiichi_1803111.html |archivedate=19 March 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"en20110412-4\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nisa.meti.go.jp/english/files/en20110412-4.pdf |title=NISA News Release April&nbsp;12,&nbsp;2011 |accessdate=24 April 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110501090736/http://www.nisa.meti.go.jp/english/files/en20110412-4.pdf |archivedate=1 May 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Frank N. von Hippel 27\u201336\">{{cite journal |url=http://bos.sagepub.com/content/67/5/27.full |titl