wissre14\">[http://media.swissre.com/documents/pr_20110321_japan_en.pdf Swiss Re provides estimate of its claims costs from Japan earthquake and tsunami], Swiss Re, news release, 21 March 2011</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Synth\u00e8se actualis\u00e9e des connaissances relatives \u00e0 l'impact sur le milieu marin des rejets radioactifs du site nucl\u00e9aire accident\u00e9 de Fukushima Dai-ichi\">{{cite web |url= http://www.irsn.fr/FR/Actualites_presse/Actualites/Documents/IRSN-NI-Impact_accident_Fukushima_sur_milieu_marin_26102011.pdf |title= Synth\u00e8se actualis\u00e9e des connaissances relatives \u00e0 l'impact sur le milieu marin des rejets radioactifs du site nucl\u00e9aire accident\u00e9 de Fukushima Dai-ichi |author= IRSN |date= 26 October 2011 |accessdate= 3 January 2012 |postscript= {{inconsistent citations}}}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TEPCO implements new safety measures in bid to restart Niigata reactors\">{{cite news |url=http://ajw.asahi.com/article/0311disaster/fukushima/AJ201310030043 |title=TEPCO implements new safety measures in bid to restart Niigata reactors |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413220421/http://ajw.asahi.com/article/0311disaster/fukushima/AJ201310030043 |archivedate=13 April 2014 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TEPCO Press Release\">{{cite web |last=TEPCO Press Release|title=The Estimated Amount of Radioactive Materials Released into the Air and the Ocean Caused by Fukushima Daiichi Nuclear Power Station Accident Due to the Tohoku-Chihou-Taiheiyou-Oki Earthquake (As of May 2012)|url=http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/press/corp-com/release/2012/1204659_1870.html|work=TEPCO|accessdate=24 May 2012 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140215101525/http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/press/corp-com/release/2012/1204659_1870.html |archivedate= 15 February 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Varma\">{{cite news|last1=Varma|first1=Subodh|title=Fukushima radiation data is wildly wrong, management apologizes|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/Fukushima-radiation-data-is-wildly-wrong-management-apologizes/articleshow/30163944.cms|accessdate=11 March 2016|agency=TNN|date=10 February 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140211124813/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/Fukushima-radiation-data-is-wildly-wrong-management-apologizes/articleshow/30163944.cms|archivedate=11 February 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TEPCO to Review Erroneous Radiation Data\">{{cite web |url=http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/science/news/20140206-OYT1T01326.htm|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=TEPCO to Review Erroneous Radiation Data |date=9 February 2014 |website=[[Yomiuri Online]] |publisher=[[Yomiuri Shimbun]] |accessdate=9 February 2014 |quote=On February 6, TEPCO announced that 5 million Bq/Liter of radioactive strontium was detected from the groundwater sample taken on June 5 last year from one of the observation wells on the embankment of Fukushima I Nuclear Power Plant. The density is 160,000 times that of the legal limit for release into the ocean, and it is about 1,000 times that of the highest density in the groundwater that had been measured so far (5,100 Bq/L). TEPCO didn't disclose the result of measurement of strontium alone, as the company believed there was a possibility that the result of measurement was wrong. As to this particular sample, TEPCO had announced on July last year that the sample had contained 900,000 Bq/L of all-beta including strontium. On February 6, TEPCO explained that they had \"underestimated all of the results of high-density all-beta, which exceeded the upper limit of measurement.\" This particular sample may contain about 10 million Bq/L of all-beta, according to TEPCO. The company recently switched to a different method of analysis that uses diluted samples when the density of radioactive materials is high.}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TEPCO to review erroneous radiation data\">{{cite web |url=http://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/english/news/20140209_80.html |archive-url=https://archive.today/20140209232503/http://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/english/news/20140209_80.html |archive-date=9 February 2014 |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=TEPCO to review erroneous radiation data |date=9 February 2014 |website=[[NHK World]] |publisher=NHK |accessdate=9 February 2014 |quote=Tokyo Electric Power Company, or TEPCO, says it has detected a record high 5 million becquerels (0.13 milli[[curie]]s)per liter of radioactive strontium in groundwater collected last July from one of the wells close to the ocean. ... Based on the result, levels of radioactive substances that emit beta particles are estimated to be 10 million becquerels (0.26 milli[[curie]]s) per liter, which is more than 10 times the initial reading. |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"tepco\">[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/press/corp-com/release/11031204-e.html \"Plant Status of Fukushima Daini Nuclear Power Station (as of 0&nbsp;AM 12 March )\", ''TEPCO'', end of day 11 April]. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140215101438/http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/press/corp-com/release/11031204-e.html |date=15 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"tepco2\">[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/press/corp-com/release/2012/1204659_1870.html Press Release |The Estimated Amount of Radioactive Materials Released into the Air and the Ocean Caused by Fukushima Daiichi Nuclear Power Station Accident Due to the Tohoku-Chihou-Taiheiyou-Oki Earthquake (As of May 2012)]. TEPCO. Retrieved on 13 February 2013. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140215101525/http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/press/corp-com/release/2012/1204659_1870.html |date=15 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"tepco6\">[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/nu/fukushima-np/images/handouts_111130_04-e.pdf The Evaluation Status of Reactor Core Damage at Fukushima Daiichi Nuclear Power Station Units 1 to 3] 30 November 2011 Tokyo Electric Power Company</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"terrapub\">{