567.htm |date=13 April 2011}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NISASummary060411\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nisa.meti.go.jp/english/files/en20110406-1-1.pdf |title=The 2011 off the Pacific coast of Tohoku Pacific Earthquake and the seismic damage to the NPPs |accessdate=13 July 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110522211409/http://www.nisa.meti.go.jp/english/files/en20110406-1-1.pdf |archivedate=22 May 2011}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"google.com\">{{cite web |author=Eric Talmadge |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Business/wireStory?id=13982317#.T9WqgFLT7NA |title=AP: First 24&nbsp;hours shaped Japan nuke crisis |work=Google.com |date=1 July 2011 |accessdate=13 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"WNN\">{{cite news |title=Massive earthquake hits Japan |url=http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS_Massive_earthquake_hits_Japan_1103111.html |accessdate=13 March 2011 |newspaper=World Nuclear News|date=11 March 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110331005918/http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS_Massive_earthquake_hits_Japan_1103111.html |archivedate=31 March 2011 |url-status=live }};</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"bwokada\">{{cite news |url=http://www.businessweek.com/news/2011-03-11/japan-orders-evacuation-from-near-nuclear-plant-after-quake.html |title=Japan Orders Evacuation From Near Nuclear Plant After Quake |author=Inajima, Tsuyoshi |author2=Okada, Yuji |work=Bloomberg BusinessWeek |date=11 March 2011 |accessdate=11 March 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120202204525/http://www.businessweek.com/news/2011-03-11/japan-orders-evacuation-from-near-nuclear-plant-after-quake.html |archivedate=2 February 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"nytimesWilson\">David Sanger and Matthew Wald, [https://www.nytimes.com/2011/03/14/world/asia/japan-fukushima-nuclear-reactor.html Radioactive releases in Japan could last months, experts say.] ''The New York Times'' 13 March 2011 {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120925004946/http://www.nytimes.com/2011/03/14/world/asia/japan-fukushima-nuclear-reactor.html |date=25 September 2012}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"tepco11b\">{{cite press release|url=http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/press/corp-com/release/11031103-e.html |title=TEPCO press release 3 |work=Tepco |date=11 March 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110319173402/http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/press/corp-com/release/11031103-e.html |archivedate=19 March 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"IAEAtsunami1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.iaea.org/newscenter/news/tsunamiupdate01.html |title=IAEA Update on Japan Earthquake |quote=As reported earlier, a 400 millisieverts (mSv) per hour radiation dose observed at Fukushima Daiichi occurred between 1s 3 and 4. This is a high dose-level value, but it is a local value at a single location and at a certain point in time. The IAEA continues to confirm the evolution and value of this dose rate. It should be noted that because of this detected value, non-indispensable staff was evacuated from the plant, in line with the Emergency Response Plan, and that the population around the plant is already evacuated. |accessdate=16 March 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110314165946/http://www.iaea.org/newscenter/news/tsunamiupdate01.html |archivedate=14 March 2011 |url-status=live |date=June 2011 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NISA61\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nisa.meti.go.jp/english/files/en20110330-1-1.pdf |title=Seismic Damage Information (the 61st Release) |date=29 March 2011 |work=Nuclear and Industrial Safety Agency |accessdate=12 April 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110501090740/http://www.nisa.meti.go.jp/english/files/en20110330-1-1.pdf |archivedate=1 May 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"world-nuclear-news.org\">{{cite web |title=Spraying continues at Fukushima Daiichi |url=http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS_Spraying_continues_at_Fukushima_Daiichi_1803111.html |accessdate=19 March 2011 |date=18 March 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110319003615/http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/RS_Spraying_continues_at_Fukushima_Daiichi_1803111.html |archivedate=19 March 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"en20110412-4\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nisa.meti.go.jp/english/files/en20110412-4.pdf |title=NISA News Release April&nbsp;12,&nbsp;2011 |accessdate=24 April 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110501090736/http://www.nisa.meti.go.jp/english/files/en20110412-4.pdf |archivedate=1 May 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Frank N. von Hippel 27\u201336\">{{cite journal |url=http://bos.sagepub.com/content/67/5/27.full |title=The radiological and psychological consequences of the Fukushima Daiichi accident |author=Frank N. von Hippel |date=2011|volume=67 |issue=5 |journal=Bulletin of the Atomic Scientists |pages=27\u201336 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120113090511/http://bos.sagepub.com/content/67/5/27.full |archivedate=13 January 2012 |url-status=live |bibcode=2011BuAtS..67e..27V |doi=10.1177/0096340211421588 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Aus2\">{{cite journal |title= Stealthy, silent destroyer of DNA |journal= [[The Australian]] |date= 16 March 2011 |first= Adam |last= Cresswell |postscript= {{inconsistent citations}}}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"newscientist.com\">[https://www.newscientist.com/article/dn20285-fukushima-radioactive-fallout-nears-chernobyl-levels.html Fukushima radioactive fallout nears Chernobyl levels \u2013 24 March 2011]. New Scientist. Retrieved 30 April 2011. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110326000631/http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn20285-fukushima-radioactive-fallout-nears-chernobyl-levels.html |date=26 March 2011}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"seattletimes.nwsource.com\">Doughton, Sandi. (5 April 2011) [http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/localnews/2014693490_nukemonitors06m.html Local News|Universities come through in monitoring for radiation|Seattle Times Newspaper]. Seattletimes.nwsource.com. Retrieved 30 April 2011. {