011 |work=Bellona |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318044157/http://www.bellona.org/articles/articles_2011/rad_forcasts_ignored |archivedate=18 March 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"evac\">{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/world/la-fgw-japan-nuclear-plant-20110326,0,5763742.story|title=Japan steps up nuclear plant precautions; Kan apologizes|date=25 March 2011|work=Los Angeles Times|author=Makinen, Julie}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"bks2011\">Benjamin K. Sovacool (2011). ''[[Contesting the Future of Nuclear Power]]: A Critical Global Assessment of Atomic Energy'', [[World Scientific]], p. 287.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"bb20110916\">{{cite news |title=Japan Plans Floating Wind Power Plant |url=http://www.breakbulk.com/wind-renewables/japan-plans-floating-wind-power-plant |accessdate=12 October 2011 |newspaper=Breakbulk |date=16 September 2011 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120521071742/http://www.breakbulk.com/wind-renewables/japan-plans-floating-wind-power-plant |archivedate= 21 May 2012 |url-status=dead}}</ref>}}\n\n===Sources===\n'''Cited'''\n* {{cite book|url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/78218/1/9789241505130_eng.pdf |title=Health risk assessment from the nuclear accident after the 2011 Great East Japan Earthquake and Tsunami |last=WHO|year=2013 |isbn=978-9241505130 |location=|pages=|ref=harv|via=|accessdate=7 September 2016}}\n\n'''Other'''\n* [[Caldicott, Helen]] [ed.]: ''Crisis Without End: The Medical and Ecological Consequences of the Fukushima Nuclear Catastrophe.'' [From the \"Symposium at the [[New York Academy of Medicine]], March 11\u201312, 2013\"]. The New Press, 2014. {{ISBN|978-1-59558-970-5}} (eBook)\n* Nadesan, Majia (2013). ''[https://www.palgrave.com/gp/book/9781137343116 Fukushima and the Privatization of Risk]''. London, Palgrave, 2013. {{ISBN|978-1137343116}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Fukushima I accidents}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n\n===Investigation===\n* [http://warp.da.