 Aur Barbareek]]''\n| [[Arjuna]]\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[I Don't Watch TV (web series)|I Don't Watch TV]]''\n|Himself\n|\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name |1019296|Arjun}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Arjun}}\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male television actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=September 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Firoz Khan\n| image = Arjun feroz khan 2014-02-20 16-56.jpg\n| imagesize =\n| caption = \n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = \n| residence = \n| occupation = [[Actor]]\n| years_active = 1984&ndash;present\n| website = \n| spouse = \n| children = \n\n| height = \n}}\n'''Firoz Khan''' is an [[India]]n actor, best known for playing the hero character of [[Arjuna]] in [[B. R. Chopra]]'s television serialisation of the ancient Indian history ''[[Mahabharat (1988 TV series)|Mahabharat]]''.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-01-20/tv/30646770_1_marathi-films-film-industry-small-screen |title=A film on Mahabharata |publisher=The Times Of India |date=20 January 2012 |accessdate=2012-04-18}}</ref> He has also acted in a number of [[Hindi language]] movies.\n\nHe is an alumnus of Smt. MMK College of Commerce and Economics.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mmkcollege.org/alumni-esteemed.asp |title=Alumni |publisher=Smt. MMK College of Commerce & Economics |accessdate=2012-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Other notes\n|-\n| 1984\n| ''[[Manzil Manzil]]''\n| Rupesh\n|\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''[[Zabardast]]''\n| Bikram Singh\n|\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''[[Swati (1986 film)|Swati]]''\n| Manohar Joshi\n|\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''[